Hajiya A’Isha Nagoda, mother to Amin .K. Abdul Yassar, the Director General, Media and Publicity to Kano state governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje has been reported dead. A terse statement by Mr. Yassar on behalf of his family stated that his aged mother gave up the ghost on Saturday night. The Director General Media and Publicity disclosed that barring any last minute change “my beloved mother will be interred on Sunday. Shortly after Yassar’s announcement, it has been outpouring of condolence message by sympathisers. In a condolence message, Yassar’s principal, and Kano state governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje Abdullahi Umar Ganduje described the demise of Hajiya Aisha Nagoda as a great loss. Ganduje said “She was indeed a very disciplined mother, whose life, was well spent within the family and beyond, as a turning point to many. Her righteous life moulded many, both within and outside the family,” Ganduje noted that, “Her death is a great loss to all of us. Hajiya Aisha Nagoda was a strong pillar, unifier, a gentle woman of rewarding substance and a mother to all.” “It is therefore on behalf of the government and people of Kano state, I, Abdullahi Umar Ganduje, expressing our heartfelt pain and at the same time praying for Allah’s Forgiveness and Blessings to the gentle soul of the deceased. -Advertisement- POLL Similarly, Sports Writers Association of Nigeria SWAN Kano chapter in a message signed by Abdulgafar Oladimeji. Esq. Secretary of the Association “pray umto Allah to grant you and members of.your family and friends the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss.”